If a fetal death occurs after a gestation period of 20 weeks or more, then within 72 hours after delivery, a certificate of fetal death shall be filed by:
The mortician who first takes custody of a fetus;
The person in charge of the institution or the person's designated representative when a fetus is delivered in an institution;
The physician in attendance at or immediately after delivery when a fetus is delivered outside an institution; or
The medical examiner when a fetal death occurs without medical attendance at or immediately after the delivery when a medical examiner's inquiry is required.
